N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4830.19 - Surrender of license when revoked or suspended

State Regulations

When a license is suspended or revoked the licensee shall
surrender its license to the governing body or the commission, whichever
revoked or suspended the same, on or before the effective date of the
suspension or revocation. No license shall be valid beyond the effective date
of the suspension or revocation. Notes
